<h2 id="best-practices">Best practices</h2>
<h3 id="when-to-use">When to use</h3>
<p><strong>On landing pages and home pages.</strong> The section component is a good option for distinguishing sections of content on full-width landing pages.</p>
<h3 id="when-not-to-use">When not to use</h3>
<p><strong>On interior content pages.</strong> The section component is not a generic wrapper for content, and should not be used inside containers that are already boxed and centered (use a <a href="/content/callout">callout</a> instead). It is specifically to create internally boxed sections with a full-bleed background that spans the full window width.</p>
<h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>
