<h3 id="background-image">Background image</h3>
<p>Background images can be used instead of the watermark pattern with the <code>background</code> slot. It is recommended to use a <code>picture</code> or <code>video</code> element with <code>source</code> children that specify optimized files at different breakpoints.</p>
<p>In most cases, background images impart a &quot;dark&quot; average color and thus need light text, so the <code>data-theme</code> attribute should almost always be set to <code>dark</code>. If it is not explicitly set to <code>light</code>, it will be set to <code>dark</code> automatically.</p>
<p>If the contrast is still not sufficient between the background and the text, use the <code>overlay</code> attribute and one or any of the values <code>darken</code>, <code>desaturate</code>, or <code>bottom-gradient</code>.</p>

